SIMPLE: sharply
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sharply
<hw>Sharp"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a sharp manner,; keenly;
acutely.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They are more <qex>sharply</qex> to be chastised and reformed than
the rude Irish.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The soldiers were <qex>sharply</qex> assailed with wants.</q>
<rj><qau>Hayward.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You contract your eye when you would see <qex>sharply</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sharpness</ent>⟦br⟧
